A vintage 1950s-style safety poster illustration showing a mischievous cartoon character in mechanic's overalls sneaking into a massive industrial control room filled with oversized brass gears, spinning dials, and steam pipes. The character holds a wrench while reaching toward a prominent red lever marked with warning symbols. In the background, a control panel sparks dangerously. The color palette uses muted yellows, reds, and browns with halftone dot printing effects typical of mid-century industrial safety campaigns. The scene conveys playful danger and forbidden tinkering, with dramatic shadows and exaggerated perspective emphasizing the precarious situation.
